{"word":"κήδειος","slug":"κήδειος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κήδειος</b></el> <el>(κήδειος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κῆδος'><el>κῆδος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>cared for, dear, beloved</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>careful of</i>, or <i>caring for</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>of a funeral</i> or <i>tomb, mourning, sepulchral</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}